	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />May i "penetrate" into the conversation (lol) and say some things NESICIDE2 lacks:
<br />
<br />* Old NESICIDE had a pattern drawer, assembly maker (joining 4 patterns) and nametable drawer. The Graphics Bank designer is messy, unconfortable and very difficult for people who don't know a bit of 6502 asm!
<br />
<br />*The same thing with sprites. It also had a rom designer where you chose your mapper, additional VRAM on/off, SaveRAM, Trainer. Also: Ifound no support for TRAINER banks. To be honest, NESICIDE1 was like making PRG,CHR,draw,code,compile,yay! NESICIDE2 is so... "naked". 
<br />
<br />We know you are a good programmer, cpow, we saw it on NESICIDE1, but NESICIDE2 is screwed up.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


