<br />
<br />Well for one, it actually works(I'm using linux). I can't find any downloads for the source or anything for v2, and there are no instructions on how to build it from the git repository. I also like the layout and the low-level feel of v1. Not to mention the built-in pallete/sprite editor. As for those demos/examples, none of them worked with a windows build of v2 running under WINE, and they won't open in v1.

		

		</td>
