	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>cpow</b> [ Tue Aug 30, 2011 8:35 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: How to use NESICIDE 1?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">keelx wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Well for one, it actually works(I'm using linux). I can't find any downloads for the source or anything for v2, and there are no instructions on how to build it from the git repository. I also like the layout and the low-level feel of v1. Not to mention the built-in pallete/sprite editor. As for those demos/examples, none of them worked with a windows build of v2 running under WINE, and they won't open in v1.</div>
<br />
<br />Yes you bring up a good point.  NESICIDE 2 did at one time build in Linux but it has been a long while since I've gone back to Linux.  I only have a VirtualBox Ubuntu to work with...
<br />
<br />I have decided to put energy into the palette/tile editor for NESICIDE 2.
<br />
<br />I don't know about NESICIDE's capabilities over WINE.  I know the examples all work for me.  If you could post specifically what it is that is "not working" I can look into it.
<br />
<br />NESICIDE 2 is not "the continuance of" NESICIDE 1.  They are completely disjoint and incompatible packages.  The project file format of NESICIDE 1 is Windows-binary-specific.  The project file format of NESICIDE 2 is XML.
<br />
<br />Thanks for the feedback!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


